Leading British car and engine maker Rolls-Royce  plc is to team up with Hong Kong-based trading and investment firm MKI Corp.  Ltd. to pursue power generation projects in China, MKI said on Monday.
Through MKI which is extensively involved in infrastructure projects in  China, Roll-Royce Industrial Power Group would implement power-generation  projects in China.
The financing for these projects was to be arranged by Rolls-Royce's  financing arm, Rolls-Royce and Partners Finance Ltd., MKI said in a statement,  without given any further details.
